---
/**
 * production-ai-architecture/0001 · Figure 5 (Module 3) — AI observability: three
 * classic signals + a quality axis + per-request auditability.
 *
 * Verbatim copy of the source SVG (figure + svg + figcaption incl. footnote
 * <sup> #s4 / id="r4b"). No marker references in this figure.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="AI observability: traces of the agent-loop call tree, metrics including tokens and cost, an eval/quality signal, and per-request auditability tied to a request id."
    >
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >What you must be able to see</text
        >
        <rect
            x="24"
            y="40"
            width="148"
            height="78"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eef2f7"
            stroke="#1f3a5a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="98" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >Traces / spans</text
        >
        <text x="98" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >agent-loop call tree:</text
        >
        <text x="98" y="90" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >model + tool + retrieval</text
        >
        <text x="98" y="104" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >latency · tokens / span</text
        >
        <rect
            x="180"
            y="40"
            width="148"
            height="78"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eef2f7"
            stroke="#1f3a5a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="254" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >Metrics</text
        >
        <text x="254" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >latency (tails)</text
        >
        <text x="254" y="90" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >error / rate-limit rate</text
        >
        <text x="254" y="104" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >tokens &amp; cost / request</text
        >
        <rect
            x="336"
            y="40"
            width="148"
            height="78"
            rx="8"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.8"></rect>
        <text x="410" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Quality signal</text
        >
        <text x="410" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#6b675f">(the new axis)</text>
        <text x="410" y="90" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >eval: correct? grounded?</text
        >
        <text x="410" y="102" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >safe? golden set + online</text
        >
        <rect
            x="492"
            y="40"
            width="124"
            height="78"
            rx="8"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="1.8"></rect>
        <text x="554" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Auditability</text
        >
        <text x="554" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >prompt · context</text
        >
        <text x="554" y="90" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >model+version · tools</text
        >
        <text x="554" y="102" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >output · by request id</text
        >
        <rect x="24" y="140" width="592" height="40" rx="8" fill="#f6f4ef" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="158" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >The test: "Show me what the agent did for ticket #4471 last Tuesday — and was it
            right."</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="173" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >If you can't answer that from telemetry, you can't debug a wrong answer or pass an
            audit.</text
        >
        <rect x="24" y="198" width="592" height="36" rx="8" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="214" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >Wire format: OpenTelemetry GenAI semantic conventions (model name, token counts, tool
            calls)</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="228" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >so telemetry isn't vendor-locked. Capturing prompt/completion content is opt-in — it
            carries PII + cost weight.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The first three are the classic logs/metrics/traces. The quality signal and per-request
        auditability are what AI adds — a confident wrong answer is only debuggable if you captured
        what it saw and scored whether it was right.<sup><a href="#s4" id="r4b">4</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
